 null, null, null, null, null, null, '1', '2015-11-19 17:47:39', '31', '31', 'Complete entry'), ('183', '147', 'There is contribution with FTA Impact Pathways on influencing private commitments to sustainability', 'This project is part of the \"Corporate Commitments to Sustainability\" project undertaken by CIFOR', null, null, null, null, null, null, '1', '2015-11-24 01:05:28', '62', '62', 'Details about the collaboration with FTA have been provided'), ('184', '140', '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '1', '2016-02-20 15:48:21', '96', '96', ''), ('185', '110', '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '1', '2016-03-01 15:21:43', '162', '162', ''), ('186', '212', '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '1', '2016-03-04 15:44:22', '17', '17', ''), ('187', '120', '', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '1', '2016-03-08 15:25:12', '21', '21', ''), ('188', '250', 'Apart from the FP3 Impact Pathway (Low Emissions Agriculture), the project will contribute to FP1 (Climate Smart Agricultural Practices) by packaging enhancing adoption and scaling-up of CSA practices, to FP2 (Climate Risk management) via improved food supply and to FP4 (Policies & Institutions) by informing policy makers.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '1', '2016-08-18 07:53:32', '521', '521', ''), ('189', '251', 'Possible collaboration with other CRPs and thus contribution to other CCAFS Impact Pathways will be defined during the start-up phase of the project in the remainder of 2016. A linkage with FP1 scenarios as well as collaboration with PIM seem obvious choices, however, how to give body to this remains to be defined.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '1', '2016-08-31 08:50:56', '1061', '1061', ''), ('190', '249', 'The project will liaise with CCAFS projects focused on dairy production, like the Mitigation in livestock and low emissions development pathways in East Africa led by ILRI, that aims to determine system-specific pathways for improving animal feeding and reduce emissions per unit of output; and the Nationally Appropriate Mitigation Actions for dairy development project in Kenya, led by ICRAF that aims to develop implementable strategies for reducing GHG emissions intensities from dairy production. Information and experience on emission measurement, and appropriate farm management options will be exchanged with both projects, as well as exchange visits and possibly joint publications.', null, null, null, null, null, null, null, '1', '2016-08-31 09:01:49', '1060', '1060', '');


